This paper deals with the comparison of two machine translation techniques, SMT and NMT, using English-Hindi and English-Bengali language pairs. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of soft-attention in the NMT model, which falls under the category of Neural Networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper evaluates the quality of translation using metrics like BLEU and TER, which are commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) as well.
